snippet.title: Formula for Surface Area of a Sphere: Video IIII (Tanton: Mathematics)
snippet.description: In this fourth video of "geometry formulas explained" we show how Archimede's deduced that the surface area of a sphere is 4*pi*r^2 after having figured a formula for its volume. (And that was video III.)
